INSERT INTO `maintenance` VALUES (448, 'Tobey Hauter', 'thauter@peoriachristian.org', 'California', '103', 'Medium (Needs attention soon)', 'Other', 'Resolved (Completed)', 'Evidently last summer several of the locks around school were sent to the locksmith for repair.  In the process----the wrong lock was put on in Room 103.  The key to that room should match Rooms 102 and 101 AND the science storage room.  Would you please locate the original lock and return it to Room 103?\r\n\r\nOr is it possible to reKey Room 103 to match everything else?\r\n\r\nThanks, Tobey', '---SELECT ONE---', '2006-09-26', '2006-09-27', 'The rooms each have a specific key, if you want into room 103, use the storage room, then unlock the main 103 door. We ran out of keys because too many people had them, so we had to take the cylinders to the locksmith and have keys made for them. I labelled each lock to the room number, but apparantly the locksmith put the wrong cylinder in the wrong locks, so that lock could be anywhere in the building. We did give Mrs. McGinnis a separate key to the storage room, because her key fit the main door, but not the storage door. ');
